# React Components

## Before adding a component

1. Check `src/components/` for something to extend.
2. Match patterns in `MovieCard`, `MovieGrid`, `PosterImage`, `SearchBar`.

## Server vs client

- Default: Server Component (no `"use client"`).
- Client only for `useState`, `useEffect`, event handlers, or `useRouter` / `useSearchParams`.

## Props and types

- Named export with typed props; import types from `@/types/`.
- Presentation components stay pure — data and callbacks via props.

## Styling and a11y

- Tailwind utilities; zinc/amber palette (see `nextjs-typescript-tailwind` rule).
- Interactive elements need accessible labels (`aria-label`, visible text, or `alt`).

## Posters

- External poster URLs use plain `<img>` with `onError` fallback (`PosterImage`) — not `next/image`.
- Meaningful `alt` from movie title.

## Imports

- Path aliases `@/components/...`, `@/types/...`.
- No shadcn/ui or external UI libraries unless requested.

## Tests

- Add colocated `ComponentName.test.tsx`; follow `vitest-unit-testing` rule.
